                                            SUBWAY ENVIRONMENT SIMULATION
                                                  SIMULATION OF
                         SES v4.1 file for illustrating the behaviour of axial fans.
                         A contrived example for a set of notes on some oddities in SES.  Axial fans
                         are located in vent segments.  Vent segments have subsegments with different
                         temperatures (and thus different air densities).  Which subsegment's density
                         is used to adjust the fan characteristic during fire runs?
                         This file has symmetrical tunnels and two ventilation shafts with fans
                         extracting air past two fires.  Shaft 902 is connected to atmosphere at its
                         forward end, shaft 904 is connected to atmosphere at its back end.  Both
                         fans are set to draw air out of the tunnel.
                         Is the air flow symmetrical?  Yes.
                         It turns out that the axial/centrifugal fans are taken to be at the mean air
                         density in the vent section.  So the orientation of a shaft doesn't matter.
                         The mean temperature is calculated in lines 122 to 139 of PINPNT.FOR and the
                         ratio to outside air temperature is used as a proxy for mean density ratio in
                         lines 27 to 37 of OMEGA1.FOR.
                                    DESIGN TIME 1700 HRS   JULY       2020
                                                       A private, offline version of SES.  Developed
                                                       to test various modifications and to learn about
                                                       SES.  Based on SES v4.1.  All modifications by
                                                       Ewan Bennett.
                offline-SES input file version                             204.6
                              This file has a number of bugs fixed and improved
                              printouts.  It derates jet fans in fire segments
                              according to the local air density in fire runs.
                              It prints mean temperature ratio in vent segments,
                              has a "-debug1" command-line option and prints a
                              table of train pressure drops after the table of
                              section pressure drops.

                                             FAN PERFORMANCE CURVE FIT COEFFICIENTS
                                             --------------------------------------
    THE COEFFICIENTS C1, C2, C3, C4 FIT THE FAN PERFORMANCE CURVE OF THE FOLLOWING EQUATION -
          C1 * (Q**3) + C2 * (Q**2) + C3 * (Q) + C4 = P
    WHERE Q IS THE AIRFLOW RATE (CFS) OF INFLOW (EXHAUST) OR OUTFLOW (SUPPLY)
          P IS THE PRESSURE HEAD IN FT**2/SEC**2
                                        C1                  C2                  C3                  C4
    OUTFLOW (EXHAUST)             -0.1129638E-06       0.9699339E-03      -0.4317736E+01       0.2269712E+05
    -----------------
    INFLOW (SUPPLY)               -0.2275951E-06      -0.9782931E-03      -0.2166684E+01      -0.5674279E+04
    ---------------
